ClassLass,<br><br>
There was no greater meaning in the death of these men.  The problem was the Russians carried files on who they wanted and we were told they would love to have the opportunity to pick our brains about information that had nothing to do with Vietnam.<br><br>
All men are worthy of rescue.  Some can not afford to be captured.  Many flew and took the risk just for the $500 a month combat pay deduction.  I used to haul them myself.  They didn't help just rode.  Made the mission a bitch when you copilot was at home. One sortie a month.  Promotion was another.  All rated flew at least once a month if they wanted.  You had to meet your gate of years and hours.<br><br>
With each flight was risk.  The rescue would have been done for anyone.  The man is worth the effort.  Don't we wish everyone gave his fellow man this worth.
